# Environment Configuration Template

## Backend Environment Variables (.env)

# Server Configuration
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=5000

# Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/collabzy

# JWT Secrets (CHANGE THESE IN PRODUCTION!)
JWT_SECRET=your_very_long_and_secure_jwt_secret_min_32_chars
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your_very_long_and_secure_refresh_secret_min_32_chars

# Razorpay Payment Gateway
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=your_razorpay_key_id
RAZORPAY_SECRET=your_razorpay_secret
RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_razorpay_webhook_secret
PLATFORM_FEE_PERCENTAGE=10

# Social Media APIs
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=your_youtube_data_api_v3_key
INSTAGRAM_CLIENT_ID=your_instagram_client_id
INSTAGRAM_CLIENT_SECRET=your_instagram_client_secret

# CORS Configuration
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173,http://localhost:3000

# Frontend URL
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173

# Email Configuration (Optional)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your_email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your_app_password

## Frontend Environment Variables (.env)

# Backend API URL
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
VITE_SOCKET_URL=http://localhost:5000

# Razorpay
VITE_RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=your_razorpay_key_id

# App Configuration
VITE_APP_NAME=Collabzy
VITE_APP_URL=http://localhost:5173

## Production Environment Variables

### Backend (.env.production)
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=5000
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://user:pass@cluster.mongodb.net/collabzy
JWT_SECRET=your_production_jwt_secret_min_32_chars_very_strong
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your_production_refresh_secret_min_32_chars_very_strong
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_live_xxxxxxxxxxxxx
RAZORPAY_SECRET=your_production_razorpay_secret
RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_production_webhook_secret
PLATFORM_FEE_PERCENTAGE=10
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=your_youtube_api_key
INSTAGRAM_CLIENT_ID=your_instagram_client_id
INSTAGRAM_CLIENT_SECRET=your_instagram_client_secret
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://collabzy.vercel.app,https://www.collabzy.com
FRONTEND_URL=https://collabzy.vercel.app

### Frontend (.env.production)
VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend.onrender.com/api
VITE_SOCKET_URL=https://your-backend.onrender.com
VITE_RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_live_xxxxxxxxxxxxx
VITE_APP_NAME=Collabzy
VITE_APP_URL=https://collabzy.vercel.app

## How to Get API Keys

### MongoDB Atlas
1. Go to https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas
2. Create account and cluster
3. Get connection string from Connect button

### Razorpay
1. Go to https://razorpay.com
2. Sign up and create account
3. Get API keys from Settings → API Keys
4. Use Test Mode keys for development
5. Use Live Mode keys for production

### YouTube Data API
1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com
2. Create project
3. Enable YouTube Data API v3
4. Create credentials (API Key)

### Instagram Graph API
1. Go to https://developers.facebook.com
2. Create app
3. Add Instagram product
4. Get Client ID and Secret

## Security Notes

1. Never commit .env files to version control
2. Use .env.example as template (without real values)
3. Use strong, random strings for JWT secrets (min 32 chars)
4. In production, use secrets management (e.g., Render secrets, Vercel env vars)
5. Rotate API keys regularly
6. Use test mode for payment gateways during development
7. Keep production and development credentials separate

## JWT Secret Generation

Generate strong JWT secrets using Node.js:

```javascript
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"
```

Or use online tools:
- https://randomkeygen.com/ (use Fort Knox Passwords)
- https://www.grc.com/passwords.htm

## Environment Variable Validation

The backend validates required environment variables on startup.
See `backend/config/security.config.js` for validation logic.
